  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> water to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>cinnamon</strong>, <strong>ground</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and plenty of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a mixing bowl</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-size pieces and add them to the bowl of spices</p>\r\n<p>Heat a pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle&nbsp;of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the spice-coated <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 2 min or until the chicken has browned a little, then transfer the browned chicken to a plate and keep the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> with&nbsp;a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 4-5 min, or until the onions have softened slightly</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>tomatoes</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/433_step--4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
